quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Gracious (Allah)
  55,2,Who taught (mankind) the Qur’an
  55,3,created human
  55,4,and taught human persuasive speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon (run on their fixed courses) for reckoning
  55,6,The stars and the trees both prostrate
  55,7,"And He has raised the heaven high, and He has set up the balance"
  55,8,so that you may not transgress in the balance
  55,9,Establish the weight with justice and don’t give less in measurement
  55,10,And He has put the earth for the creatures
  55,11,"therein are fruits, date-palms with sheathed fruit-stalks"
  55,12,and corn with leaves and stalk for food and sweet-scented plants
  55,13,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,14,He created man from sounding clay like the clay of pottery
  55,15,and He created the jinns from smokeless flame of fire
  55,16,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,17,(He is) the Lord of the 2 easts (places of sunrise during summer and winter) and the Lord of the 2 wests (places of sunset during summer and winter)
  55,18,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,19,He has let loose the 2 seas (salt water and sweet water) meeting together
  55,20,"Yet, between them is a barrier which none of them can transgress"
  55,21,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,22,Both pearl and coral come out of them
  55,23,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,24,And the ships are His going and coming in the seas like mountains
  55,25,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,26,Everyone who is on it (earth) will perish
  55,27,and the Face (authority) of your Lord will remain full of Majesty and Honor forever
  55,28,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,29,Whoever is in the heavens and on earth begs of Him (for needs). Every day He is engaged in some matter (task)
  55,30,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,31,"We shall attend to you (give account), O you 2 classes (jinns and mankind)"
  55,32,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,33,"O assembly of jinns and mankind! If you have the power to pass beyond the zones of the heavens and the earth (to escape punishment), then pass them! But you will never be able to pass them, except with authority (from Allah)"
  55,34,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,35,"The smokeless flames of fire and molten brass will be sent against you both (jinns and mankind), and you will not be able to defend yourselves"
  55,36,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,37,When the heaven will burst and it becomes rosy (or red) like red hide
  55,38,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,39,On that Day neither human nor jinn will be asked about their sins (their faces will be either white (for Paradise) or black (for hell)
  55,40,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,41,The sinners will be recognized by their marks (black faces) and they will be seized by their forelocks and their feet
  55,42,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,43,"(It will be said to them): “This is hell which the sinners had denied it.”"
  55,44,They will go around between it (hell) and the boiling hot water
  55,45,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,46,"But for those who fear the standing before their Lord, there will be 2 gardens (in Paradise)"
  55,47,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,48,With spreading branches (of shady trees)
  55,49,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,50,In both of them 2 springs will be flowing
  55,51,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,52,In both of them there will be every kind of fruit in pairs
  55,53,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,54,They will recline on couches whose inner livings will be of silk brocade and the fruits of the 2 gardens will be near at hand
  55,55,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,56,Therein will be chaste virgins restraining their glances (upon their husbands only) whom no human or jinn has touched them before
  55,57,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,58,They are (in beauty) like rubies and coral
  55,59,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,60,Is there any reward for good other than good
  55,61,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,62,Besides these 2 there shall be 2 other gardens (in Paradise)
  55,63,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,64,(shaded with) dark green (trees)
  55,65,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,66,In both of them there will be 2 springs gushing out water
  55,67,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,68,"In each of them there will be fruits, date-palms, and pomegranates"
  55,69,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,70,Therein will be chaste and beautiful (virgins)
  55,71,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,72,Beautiful virgins (Huris) guarded in pavilions
  55,73,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,74,Whom no human or jinn has touched them before
  55,75,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,76,Reclining on green cushions and rich beautiful mattresses
  55,77,Then which of your Lord’s favors will you both (jinns and human) deny
  55,78,"Blessed is the name of your Lord (Allah), the Owner of Majesty and Honor"